INSERT [dbo].[AssociatedDocumentationCategoryPage] ([Id], [Content], [CategoryField], [Title]) VALUES (8, N'<p>Rokono Control is an open source project management system that combines lots of different features. Its based over the agile project management methodologies and the default planning workflow follows the pattern of Epic-&gt;Feature-&gt;User Story -&gt; Task | Bug | Issue. It offers dynamic user interface allowing to manage multiple projects at the same time, assign team members, manage member rights. One of its core features is to connect team members while allowing agile workflow during the development of the product that you''re working on, thus we are integrating internal messaging systems so you can connect with your team members without the use of third party applications. I am also working on personalized experiences so that developers can focus on their work while administrators focus on user rights management and managers can focus on planning boards and investors can focus on dashboards with charts that show their project progress. The software comes with a set of tools that allow server administrators to easily backup all projects and move them to a different server instance on the fly.</p><p><br></p><p><img src="http://localhost:6005/Files/Uploads/logo.png"></p>', 7, N'What does RokonoControl embody as a goal?')
GO
INSERT [dbo].[AssociatedDocumentationCategoryPage] ([Id], [Content], [CategoryField], [Title]) VALUES (9, N'<p>It is really important to always stick with our latest release to follow the best security practices and latest features. Thus we provide an optional download link on our official web page and as well as release downloaded on our GitHub repository. As per usual we ship Rokono Control as a standalone application however you will need to setup few stuff in order to get the application working out of the box, The first thing that you need to do is to follow these links and make sure that you have everything setup in order to get started with installing the software.</p><p><br></p><ul><li>.Net core 3.1 - https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download</li><li>A working version of NGINX/Kestrel or any other form of hosting that you can start RokonoControl Behind For NGINX : https://www.nginx.com/</li><li>A working database provider, it can be self hosted or a  cloud instance, you must  have the database of your choice ready to go before installing the software.</li><li>A working email address that allows outbound traffic over TLS, the port of the email provider STMP IMAP</li><li>An SSL certificate certbot or paid one.</li></ul><p><br></p><p>Once you have installed all the requirments to get the web platform installed you may proceed to installing the software. </p>', 8, N'Getting your everything you need before doing a new setup. ')
GO
INSERT [dbo].[AssociatedDocumentationCategoryPage] ([Id], [Content], [CategoryField], [Title]) VALUES (10, N'<p>First we need to make sure that our latest build is okay, usually our project management module handle this on each push to the Master branch however we want to be that its running while we are building from source.</p><p><br></p><p>Please follow the following steps:</p><p><br></p><ul><li>Open the console</li><li>Type dotnet --Help. It should being the version of the tool that you have installed, make sure that its 3.1 or later then proceed</li><li>Navigate inside the cloned folder / Platform inside the platform folder run the following commands</li><li>Choose your database provider by deploying our database to your own server </li></ul><pre class="ql-syntax" spellcheck="false">Don''t forget to scaffold your own context as the default project uses sql server by default and there is no need to scaffold the context however if you are trying to deploy with MYSQL  make sure to run the next command 

</pre><ul><li>dotnet build - if there are no errors / warnings please proceed further with</li><li>dotnet publish -c Release -r linux-x64</li><li>Navigate inside /bin/Release/netcorapp3.1/publish this would be our default release folder you can take the content of this folder and deploy it on your server</li><li>Open a remote access or any of ftp clients then navigate to your server installation folder</li><li>Copy the content of the publish directory to the server</li><li>Open appsettings.Development.json and enter your email data, then do the following with your password</li><li>Now add your database connection string to your application</li><li>Save the changes and close the file</li><li>Now simply start the systemctl service if you''re using linux and your instance should be working</li></ul>', 8, N'Installing the software from GitHub Master')
GO
INSERT [dbo].[AssociatedDocumentationCategoryPage] ([Id], [Content], [CategoryField], [Title]) VALUES (11, N'<p>In order to install the software from binary you must have setup your database, navigate inside the database and make sure that your administration tool is working by getting the list of all projects. </p><p><br></p><p>If it says that there are no projects its most likely working fine, now you must connect the database to your newly downloaded application</p><p><br></p><ul><li>Go to the folder of the archive and extract it.</li><li>Once extracted open appsettings.Development.json </li><li>Change the connection string to match your matching your selected database please follow the following links for the different databases setup options <a href="#MSSQL" target="_blank"><u>MSSQL </u></a><a href="#MYSQL" target="_blank"><u>MYSQL</u></a></li><li>Change your email credentials and setup your STMP port followed by IMAP address.</li><li>Close the file</li><li>Take the folder and add it inside IIS</li><li>Setup the program to run over  a specific port then just click start and it should be good to go.</li></ul>', 8, N'Installing from binary - Windows ')
GO
INSERT [dbo].[AssociatedDocumentationCategoryPage] ([Id], [Content], [CategoryField], [Title]) VALUES (12, N'<p>In order to install the software from binary you must have setup your database, navigate inside the database and make sure that your administration tool is working by getting the list of all projects.</p><p><br></p><p>If it says that there are no projects its most likely working fine, now you must connect the database to your newly downloaded application</p><p><br></p><ul><li>Go to the folder of the archive and extract it.</li><li>Once extracted open appsettings.Development.json</li><li>Change the connection string to match your matching your selected database please follow the following links for the different databases setup options <a href="http://localhost:6005/Documentation/Index?Id=5012#MSSQL" target="_blank"><u>MSSQL </u></a><a href="http://localhost:6005/Documentation/Index?Id=5012#MYSQL" target="_blank"><u>MYSQL</u></a></li><li>Change your email credentials and setup your STMP port followed by IMAP address.</li><li>Close the file</li><li>Take the folder that you just created and add it inside your favorite sftp client, then upload the content to your server main hosting directory</li><li>Connect to the server via SSH, once connected go to your nginx configuration settings /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default</li><li>open the file and add a reverse proxy followed looking up to your personal/company domain name or ip address. </li><li>save the changes and close the file.</li><li>go back two levels and enter inside system directory /etc/system/systemd</li><li>create a new service that will handle the automatic starting, restarting and log of the current application</li><li>save the file as RokonoControl.servoce and close it</li><li>restart nginx</li><li>Systemctl start RokonoControl,service </li><li>navigate to the pointed domain/ip address name and you will be presented with the latest version of RokonoControl</li><li>Setup the program to run over a specific port then just click start and it should be good to go.</li></ul><p><br></p>', 8, N'Installing under Linux')
